4. JFrog + AWS ECR	Mirror/proxy ECR through Artifactory

Here are the steps to mirror/proxy AWS ECR through JFrog Artifactory on your personal laptop:

Prerequisites
Install JFrog Artifactory (OSS or Pro Trial)

# Using Docker (easiest for local)
docker run -d --name artifactory \
  -p 8081:8081 -p 8082:8082 \
  -v artifactory-data:/var/opt/jfrog/artifactory \
  releases-docker.jfrog.io/jfrog/artifactory-oss:latest

Access at http://localhost:8082 (default creds: admin/password)

AWS CLI configured with credentials that have ECR read access:
aws configure
# or use ~/.aws/credentials

Step 1 — Get ECR Auth Token
aws ecr get-login-password --region <your-region>
# Save this token — it's valid for 12 hours

Step 2 — Create a Remote Docker Repository in Artifactory
Go to Administration → Repositories → Remote → New Remote Repository

Select Docker

Fill in:

Field	Value
Repository Key	ecr-proxy
URL	https://<account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com
Username	AWS
Password	(paste the token from Step 1)
Enable Token Authentication	✓
Under Advanced, set Block Mismatching Mime Types if needed

Save

Step 3 — Create a Virtual Repository (Optional but Recommended)
Go to Repositories → Virtual → New
Select Docker, key: docker-virtual
Add ecr-proxy as an included repository
Set as Default Deployment Repo if desired

Step 4 — Configure Docker to Use Artifactory as Registry
# Login to Artifactory's Docker registry
docker login localhost:8082 -u admin -p <artifactory-password>

Add to daemon.json (or Docker Desktop settings):
{
  "insecure-registries": ["localhost:8082"]
}
Restart Docker daemon if needed.

Step 5 — Pull Images via the Proxy
# Instead of pulling directly from ECR:
# docker pull <account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/myimage:tag

# Pull through Artifactory:
docker pull localhost:8082/ecr-proxy/myimage:tag
Artifactory will fetch from ECR, cache it, and serve future pulls locally.

Step 6 — Automate Token Refresh (ECR tokens expire in 12h)
Create a cron job or script:
#!/bin/bash
TOKEN=$(aws ecr get-login-password --region <region>)

curl -u admin:<admin-pass> -X POST \
  "http://localhost:8082/artifactory/api/repositories/ecr-proxy" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"password\": \"$TOKEN\"}"

  Schedule with crontab -e:
  0 */11 * * * /path/to/refresh-ecr-token.sh

  Key Notes
Free OSS tier supports remote repos but lacks some enterprise features
ECR requires the AWS username with the short-lived token as password
If using Artifactory Cloud (free tier) instead of local Docker, the setup is the same but URL changes to your cloud instance
For production, use IAM roles or credential rotation instead of static tokens
